{"title_page": "Tom Williamson (English footballer)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Tom Williamson\n| image =\n| fullname = Thomas Williamson<ref name=Hugman>{{Hugman|21345|accessdate=31 December 2018}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1984|12|24|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Leicester]], England\n| height = \n| currentclub = [[Basingstoke Town F.C.|Basingstoke Town]]\n| clubnumber = \n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| youthyears1 =   \n| youthclubs1 =   [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]]\n| years1 = 2002\u20132004 \n| clubs1 = [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] \n| caps1 = 1\n| goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2004\u20132005 \n| clubs2 = [[Canvey Island F.C.|Canvey Island]]  \n| caps2 = 12\n| goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2005\u20132007 \n| clubs3 = [[Grays Athletic F.C.|Grays Athletic]] \n| caps3 = 32\n| goals3 = 1\n| years4 = 2007\u20132008 \n| clubs4 = [[Bishop's Stortford F.C.|Bishop's Stortford]] \n| caps4 = \n| goals4 = \n| years5 = 2008\u20132011\n| clubs5 = [[Basingstoke Town F.C.|Basingstoke Town]]\n| caps5 = \n| goals5 = \n| club-update = 12:40, 29 July 2008 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Thomas Williamson''' (born 24 December 1984) is an English [[association football|footballer]] who played in the [[Premier League]] for [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]].<ref>{{Soccerbase season|30788|2001|accessdate=31 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nReleased by Leicester in 2004, he spent a year at [[Canvey Island F.C.|Canvey Island]] and two at [[Grays Athletic F.C.|Grays Athletic]] before his contract was terminated by mutual consent on 3 August 2007.<ref name=Grays>{{cite web |url=http://www.graysath-online.com/stats/player.php?id=24 |title=Profile: Tom Williamson |website=Grays Athletic FC Statistics Archive |accessdate=31 December 2018}}</ref> He joined [[Bishop's Stortford F.C.|Bishop's Stortford]] for the 2007\u201308 season.\n\nIn July 2008, Williamson signed for [[Basingstoke Town F.C.|Basingstoke Town]].<ref name=\"Gray reunites with Williamson\">{{cite news | title = Gray reunites with Williamson | url = http://www.nonleaguedaily.com/news/index.php?newsmode=FULL&nid=51594 | publisher = NonLeagueDaily.com | date = 29 July 2008 | accessdate = 29 July 2008}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n'''Grays Athletic'''\n*[[FA Trophy]]: [[2005\u201306 FA Trophy|2005\u201306]]<ref name=Grays/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Williamson, Tom}}\n[[Category:1984 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Leicester]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Leicester City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Canvey Island F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Grays Athletic F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bishop's Stortford F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Basingstoke Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:National League (English football) players]]\n\n\n{{England-footy-midfielder-1980s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Tom Williamson\n| image =\n| fullname = Thomas Williamson<ref name=Hugman>{{Hugman|21345|accessdate=31 December 2018}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1984|12|24|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Leicester]], England\n| height = {{height|ft=5|in=9}}\n| currentclub = [[Basingstoke Town F.C.|Basingstoke Town]]\n| clubnumber = \n| position = [[Midfielder (football)|Midfielder]]\n| youthyears1 =   \n| youthclubs1 =   [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]]\n| years1 = 2002\u20132004 \n| clubs1 = [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] \n| caps1 = 1\n| goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2004\u20132005 \n| clubs2 = [[Canvey Island F.C.|Canvey Island]]  \n| caps2 = 12\n| goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2005\u20132007 \n| clubs3 = [[Grays Athletic F.C.|Grays Athletic]] \n| caps3 = 32\n| goals3 = 1\n| years4 = 2007\u20132008 \n| clubs4 = [[Bishop's Stortford F.C.|Bishop's Stortford]] \n| caps4 = \n| goals4 = \n| years5 = 2008\u20132011\n| clubs5 = [[Basingstoke Town F.C.|Basingstoke Town]]\n| caps5 = \n| goals5 = \n| club-update = 12:40, 29 July 2008 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Thomas Williamson''' (born 24 December 1984) is an English [[football (soccer)|footballer]] who played in the [[Premier League]] for [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]].<ref>{{Soccerbase season|30788|2001|accessdate=31 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nReleased by Leicester in 2004, he spent a year at [[Canvey Island F.C.|Canvey Island]] and two at [[Grays Athletic F.C.|Grays Athletic]] before his contract was terminated by mutual consent on 3 August 2007.<ref name=Grays>{{cite web |url=http://www.graysath-online.com/stats/player.php?id=24 |title=Profile: Tom Williamson |website=Grays Athletic FC Statistics Archive |accessdate=31 December 2018}}</ref> He joined [[Bishop's Stortford F.C.|Bishop's Stortford]] for the 2007\u201308 season.\n\nIn July 2008, Williamson signed for [[Basingstoke Town F.C.|Basingstoke Town]].<ref name=\"Gray reunites with Williamson\">{{cite news | title = Gray reunites with Williamson | url = http://www.nonleaguedaily.com/news/index.php?newsmode=FULL&nid=51594 | publisher = NonLeagueDaily.com | date = 29 July 2008 | accessdate = 29 July 2008}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n'''Grays Athletic'''\n*[[FA Trophy]]: [[2005\u201306 FA Trophy|2005\u201306]]<ref name=Grays/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Williamson, Tom}}\n[[Category:1984 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Leicester]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Leicester City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Canvey Island F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Grays Athletic F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bishop's Stortford F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Basingstoke Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:National League (English football) players]]\