g Town F.C.|Kettering Town]]\n| caps21         = 1\n| goals21        = 0\n| years22        = 2012\u20132013\n| clubs22        = [[Notts County F.C.|Notts County]]\n| caps22         = 1 \n| goals22        = 0 \n| years23        = 2014\n| clubs23        = [[Guildford City F.C.|Guildford City]]\n| caps23         = 3\n| goals23        = 0\n| years24        = 2014\n| clubs24        = [[Amicale FC|Amicale]]\n| caps24         = \n| goals24        = \n| years25        = 2016\n| clubs25        = [[Slough Town F.C.|Slough Town]]\n| caps25         = 5\n| goals25        = 0\n| years26        = 2016\n| clubs26        = [[Arizona United SC|Arizona United]]\n| caps26         = 5\n| goals26        = 0\n| years27        = 2017\n| clubs27        = Houghton & Wyton\n| caps27         = \n| goals27        = \n| years28        = 2018\u2013\n| clubs28        = [[Hashtag United F.C.|Hashtag United]]\n| caps28         = 25<ref>{{cite web |url=http://fulltime-league.thefa.com/DisplayStatsForPlayer.do?id=905230188 |title=Thomas Williams Player Stats |publisher=The FA |accessdate=11 February 2019}}</ref>\n| goals28        = 2\n| nationalyears1 = 2006\n| nationalteam1  = [[Cyprus national football team|Cyprus]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 1\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| club-update    = 09:29, 23 April 2019 (UTC)\n}}\n\n'''Thomas Andrew Williams''' (born 8 July 1980) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Hashtag United F.C.|Hashtag United]] of the [[Essex Senior Football League|Essex Senior League]]. A [[Defender (association football)|defender]] or [[midfielder]], he made nearly 300 appearances in [[the Football League]] playing for numerous clubs.\n\nBorn in England, he represented Cyprus at international level.\n\n==Career==\n\n===Club career===\nWilliams was born in [[Carshalton]], London.<ref name=\"Hugman2003-04\"/> His professional career began with [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] in April 2000 when he joined the club from [[Walton & Hersham F.C.|Walton & Hersham]] for a fee of \u00a340,000. He went [[loan (football)|on loan]] to [[Peterborough United F.C.|Peterborough United]] in March 2001, without having made his senior debut, and the move was made permanent during the summer. He stayed with the Posh for one season, before moving to [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]] for a fee of \u00a3350,000.\n\nHis career stalled at [[St Andrew's (stadium)|St Andrew's]], playing just four games for Birmingham, and, after two loan periods at [[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|Queens Park Rangers]], during which he scored once, against [[Huddersfield Town]],<ref>{{soccerbase season|24437|2002|accessdate=29 October 2018}}</ref> he rejoined Peterborough United, initially on loan, later joining permanently. In May 2004 Williams went to [[Barnsley F.C.|Barnsley]] on a free transfer.\n\nHe played a full season for the [[South Yorkshire]] side, before moving again on a free transfer to [[Gillingham F.C.|Gillingham]] in July 2005, and then signing for [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]] in January 2006 after the Gills suffered financial problems. He returned to the side in December 2006 after a [[hernia]] operation in November, and was released at the end of the season.\n\nOn 27 July 2007, he joined [[Wycombe Wanderers F.C.|Wycombe Wanderers]] on a two-year deal.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/w/wycombe_wanderers/6919137.stm |title=Wycombe recruit defender Williams |accessdate=27 July 2007 |date=27 July 2007 |publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 December 2007 Williams joined Peterborough United for the third time, initially on an emergency loan to make him available for the match on New Year's Day, for which he was an unused substitute. The loan was converted to a permanent deal two days later.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.peterboroughtoday.co.uk/sport/Posh-signings-Williams-and-Hatch.3631028.jp |title=Posh signings: Williams and Hatch |newspaper=Peterborough Evening Telegraph |author=Swann, Alan |date=31 December 2007 |accessdate=5 March 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wycombewanderers.premiumtv.co.uk/page/LatestNews/0,,10430~1203142,00.html |title=Tom Williams leaves the club |publisher=Wycombe Wanderers F.C. |author=Cecil, Matt |date=31 December 2007 |accessdate=5 March 2008 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110809071539/https://www.wycombewanderers.co.uk/page/LatestNews/0,,10430~1203142,00.html |archivedate=9 August 2011}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 November 2009, Williams rejoined Championship side Queens Park Rangers on a short-term loan deal, with a possible view to sign permanently in the January transfer window. This did not happen in the end and he returned to Peterborough during January 2010.\n\nWilliams joined former boss [[Darren Ferguson]] at [[Preston North End]] on loan for the rest of the season. Preston decided not to sign him on a permanent basis, and he returned to Peterborough, where he was released following his contract expiry.\n\nAfter a pre-season trial,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/bristol_city/8842940.stm |title=Defender Tom Williams handed trial by Bristol City |publisher=BBC Sport |date=21 July 2010 |accessdate=6 August 2010}}</ref> Williams joined Championship club [[Bristol City F.C.|Bristol City]] on a six-month contract on 5 August 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bcfc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10327~2112311,00.html |title=Tom pens six-month deal |publisher=Bristol City F.C |date=5 August 2010 |accessdate=6 August 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100817224332/https://www.bcfc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10327~2112311,00.html |archivedate=17 August 2010}}</ref>\n\nWilliams joined [[Colchester United F.C.|Colchester United]] on a month's loan on 30 September, later extended for a further two months. He made nine appearances in all competitions and scored once, in a 2\u20131 win over [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|AFC Bournemouth]].<ref name=sb1011>{{soccerbase season|24437|2010|accessdate=29 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_2/9096845.stm |title=Bournemouth 1\u20132 Colchester |publisher=BBC Sport |date=30 October 2010 |accessdate=29 October 2018}}</ref> Williams' Bristol City contract was terminated on 5 January 2011.\n\nOn 14 February, he joined League One club [[Walsall F.C.|Walsall]] until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/w/walsall/9396859.stm |title=Walsall sign utility player Tom Williams |publisher=BBC Sport |date=14 February 2011 |accessdate=16 December 2011}}</ref> He made fourteen league appearances and scored once, in a 1\u20131 draw with [[Oldham Athletic]].<ref name=sb1011/><ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_2/13112141.stm |title=Oldham 1\u20131 Walsall |publisher=BBC Sport |date=25 April 2011 |accessdate=29 October 2018}}</ref> In August 2011, Williams played one match in the [[Conference National|Conference]] for [[Kettering Town F.C.|Kettering Town]], a 3\u20130 defeat away at [[Mansfield Town]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ketteringtownfc.co.uk/story.php?story_id=834 |title=Mansfield Town 3\u20130 Kettering Town |publisher=Kettering Town F.C |date=27 August 2011 |accessdate=16 December 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402115840/http://www.ketteringtownfc.co.uk/story.php?story_id=834 |archivedate=2 April 2015}}</ref> He signed for [[Notts County F.C.|Notts County]] in August 2012 on a short-term deal,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/19177337 |title=Notts County sign Carl Regan and Tom Williams |publisher=BBC Sport |date=8 August 2012 |accessdate=2 January 2013}}</ref> and was released in January 2013 when his contract expired.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nottscountyfc.co.uk/news/2013/january/duo-released-/ |title=Duo released |publisher=Notts County F.C. |date=2 January 2013 |accessdate=29 October 2018}}</ref>\n\nWilliams played for [[Southern Football League|Southern League Division 1 South and West]] club [[Guildford City F.C.|Guildford City]] in early 2014.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://guildfordcityfc.co.uk/2014/01/09/guildford-city-v-clevedon-town-this-saturday-new-signings/ |title=Guildford City v Clevedon Town \u2013 Today (GAME ON) & New Signings |publisher=Guildford City F.C. |date=9 January 2014 |accessdate=18 March 2015 |quote=We also welcome the highly experienced central defender Tom Williams who joins us from Notts County. Tom gained a full international cap for Cyprus in 2006 and has made nearly 300 Football League appearances for a number of clubs including Peterborough United, Barnsley and Swansea City.}}<br>{{cite web |url=http://guildfordcityfc.co.uk/2014/01/12/guildford-city-3-2-clevedon-town-match-report-by-barry-underwood/ |title=Guildford City 3\u20132 Clevedon Town |first=Barry |last=Underwood |publisher=Guildford City F.C. |date=12 January 2014 |accessdate=18 March 2015 |quote=City for their part gave a debut to Cyprus international Tom Williams in the centre of defence}}<br>{{cite web |url=http://guildfordcityfc.co.uk/2014/02/09/merthyr-town-4-12-guildford-city-0-0/ |title=Merthyr Town 12\u20130 Guildford City |publisher=Guildford City F.C. |date=9 February 2014 |accessdate=18 March 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2014, Williams was one of a number of foreign signings made by [[Vanuatu]] club [[Amicale FC|Amicale]] to strengthen their team ahead of the [[2013\u201314 OFC Champions League]] campaign.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vanuafoot.vu/News/ViewArticle/tabid/1354/Article/c4648555-67ef-4f49-9e37-7b196cbf6cba/language/fr-FR/Default.aspx |title=Amicale look to Europe for Champions League glory |publisher=Vanuatu Football Federation |date=12 February 2014 |accessdate=18 March 2015 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402102748/http://www.vanuafoot.vu/News/ViewArticle/tabid/1354/Article/c4648555-67ef-4f49-9e37-7b196cbf6cba/language/fr-FR/Default.aspx |archivedate=2 April 2015}}</ref>\n\nHe joined [[Slough Town F.C.|Slough Town]] in March 2016, making five Southern League appearances,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sloughtownfc.net/profile/2072/Tom-Williams |title=Tom Williams |publisher=Slough Town F.C. |accessdate=29 October 2018}}</ref> before making five appearances for [[Arizona United SC|Arizona United]] in the [[2016 USL season]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.phxrisingfc.com/roster_players/12224959 |title=Arizona United SC: Regular Season 2016: Tommy Williams |publisher=Phoenix Rising FC |accessdate=29 October 2018}}</ref> In September 2017 he was playing for Houghton & Wyton in the [[Cambridgeshire County Football League]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.huntspost.co.uk/sport/football/local-football-from-the-football-league-to-the-cambs-league-as-tom-williams-agrees-to-join-houghton-wyton-1-5191668 |title=Local football: From the Football League to the Cambs League as Tom Williams agrees to join Houghton & Wyton |first=Mark |last=Plummer |newspaper=Hunts Post |date=12 September 2017 |accessdate=29 October 2018}}</ref>\n\nFollowing a trial in July 2018, Williams joined [[Hashtag United F.C.|Hashtag United]] of the [[Eastern Counties League]] Division One South.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://the72.co.uk/111747/ex-birmingham-city-west-ham-player-trial-hashtag-united/ |title=Ex-Birmingham City and West Ham player on trial at Hashtag United |first=Adam |last=Major |website=the72.co.uk |date=30 July 2018 |accessdate=29 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/hashtag-utd-inside-story-rise-13425170 |title=Hashtag United: Inside story on the rise and rise of YouTube's No.1 football team |first=Matt |last=Lawless |newspaper=Daily Mirror |date=17 October 2018 |accessdate=29 October 2018}}</ref> After his first season ended with promotion as champions, Williams moved into a player/coach role for the 2019\u201320 season.<ref name=HTU1>[https://www.footballfancast.com/hashtag-united/news/hashtag-united-coaching-changes Hashtag United Coaching Changes] Hashtag United</ref> On 3 September, during an [[Essex Senior Cup]] first round win away to [[Halstead Town F.C.|Halstead Town]], Williams suffered a serious hand injury after smashing a home dressing room window after he had received a red card.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.footballfancast.com/hashtag-united/news/club-statement-regarding-incident-at-halstead-town-fc |title=Club statement regarding incident at Halstead Town FC |publisher=Hashtag United |date=4 September 2019 |accessdate=4 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n===International career===\nWilliams qualifies for [[Cyprus national football team|Cyprus]] through his mother,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Watch+out+for+Cyprus,+warns+Williams.-a0151179017 |title=Watch out for Cyprus, warns Williams |first=Phil |last=Blanche |newspaper=Western Mail |location=Cardiff |date=9 September 2006 |accessdate=23 January 2012 |via=thefreelibrary.com}}</ref> and has one international cap, which came in 2006.<ref>{{NFT player|id=15260|name=Tom Williams|accessdate=29 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nWilliams is married to former [[glamour model]] [[Nicola McLean]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.peterboroughtoday.co.uk/features/Tommy-Williams-and-Nicola-McLean.5450016.jp |title=Tommy Williams and Nicola McLean tie the knot in a TV ceremony |newspaper=Peterborough Evening Telegraph |date=11 July 2009 |accessdate=30 July 2009 |author=Reinis, Nick}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n;Hashtag United<ref name=\"HTU1\"/>\n*[[Eastern Counties League]] Division One South: [[2018\u201319 Eastern Counties Football League#Division One South (Eastern Senior League)|2018\u201319]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n*[http://www.uptheposh.com/people/1433/ Profile] at UpThePosh! The Peterborough United Database\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Williams, Tom}}\n[[Category:1980 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Carshalton]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Cypriot footballers]]\n[[Category:Cyprus international footballers]]\n[[Category:Cypriot people of English descent]]\n[[Category:Walton & Hersham F.C. players]]\n[[Category:West Ham United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Peterborough United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Birmingham City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Queens Park Rangers F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Barnsley F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Gillingham F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Swansea City A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Wycombe Wanderers F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Preston North End F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bristol City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Colchester United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Walsall F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Kettering Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Notts County F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Guildford City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Amicale F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Slough Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Phoenix Rising FC players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:National League (English football) players]]\n[[Category:Southern Football League players]]\n[[Category:USL Championship players]]\n[[Category:English people of Greek Cypriot descent]]\n[[Category:Hashtag United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English expatriate sportspeople in the United States]]\n[[Category:Expatriate soccer players in the United States]]\n[[Category:English expatriate footballers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Cypriot footballer}}\n{{for|footballers named Tommy Williams|Tommy Williams (disambiguation)}}\n{{EngvarB|date=August 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2014}}\n{{BLP sources|date=February 2014}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Tom Williams\n| image          = Williams, Tom.jpg\n| caption        = Pictured in 2011\n| fullname       = Thomas Andrew Williams<ref name=\"Hugman2003-04\">{{Cite book\n | editor-first = Barry J.\n | editor-last = Hugman\n | title = The